==English==

===Noun===
'''shotgun'''

# A [[gun]] which fires loads consisting of small metal balls, called [[shot]], from a cartridge.
# (''slang'',''uncountable'') The front passenger seat in a vehicle, next to the driver.
#: ''I've got shotgun!''

=====Translations=====
*Spanish: [[escopeta]] ''f'' (1)

===Verb===
'''shotgun'''

# (''slang'') As in smoking herbal substance; to inhale from a pipe or other smoking device, followed shortly by an exhalation into someone else's mouth.

===Transitive Verb===
'''shotgun'''

# (''baseball'') To hit the ball directly back at the pitcher.

===Interjection===

''The factual accuracy of this section is [[Wiktionary:accuracy dispute|disputed]]''

'''Shotgun!'''

# (''slang'') I claim the front passenger seat of a vehicle. (Note: only applies if the caller is in line-of-sight of said vehicle, or in situations where the caller's group is collectively thinking about the vehicle).
# (''slang'') I claim an object.

